# Week-5 README

## Overview

This week focused on building a complete custom object detection pipeline using YOLO and Label Studio. The workflow included dataset preparation, image annotation, preprocessing, model training, testing, and output video generation.

---

# Objectives

* Learn image annotation using Label Studio
* Prepare a custom YOLO dataset
* Train a pretrained YOLO model on custom classes
* Detect objects on unseen test images
* Generate prediction videos from outputs

---

# Tools and Technologies

* Ubuntu / WSL
* Python Virtual Environment
* Label Studio
* YOLOv8 (Ultralytics)
* FFmpeg
* OpenCV
* Google Colab / Local System

---

# Dataset Preparation

## Step 1: Video Processing

* Downloaded videos from YouTube
* Trimmed videos using FFmpeg
* Extracted frames from videos

Example:

```bash
ffmpeg -i video.mp4 -vf "fps=5,scale=384:-1" frames/frame_%04d.jpg
```

---

## Step 2: Dataset Splitting

Frames were divided into:

* Train set
* Validation set
* Test set

Example split:

* Train: 200 images
* Validation: 60 images
* Test: 30 images

---

# Image Annotation

## Label Studio

* Installed Label Studio in a virtual environment
* Opened interface on:

```text
http://localhost:8080
```

## Classes Used

* Car
* Person
* Cycle
* Bike

Bounding boxes were created for all selected objects.

---

# YOLO Dataset Structure

```text
dataset/
│
├── images/
│   ├── train/
│   ├── val/
│   └── test/
│
├── labels/
│   ├── train/
│   └── val/
│
└── data.yaml
```

---

# data.yaml Configuration

```yaml
path: /home/subha/dataset

train: images/train
val: images/val

names:
  0: Car
  1: person
  2: cycle
  3: bike
```

---

# Model Training

## Training Command

```bash
yolo detect train \
data=/home/subha/dataset/data.yaml \
model=yolov8n.pt \
epochs=100 \
imgsz=640
```

## Training Observations

* Training loss decreased initially
* Validation loss was monitored
* Overfitting was observed when validation loss started increasing

---

# Generated Outputs

Important files generated:

* `best.pt`
* `last.pt`
* `results.png`
* prediction outputs

Custom trained weights were saved separately for inference.

---

# Object Detection on Test Images

## Prediction Command

```bash
yolo detect predict \
model=runs/detect/train/weights/best.pt \
source=/home/subha/dataset/images/test \
save=True
```

Outputs were generated with bounding boxes around detected objects.

---

# Video Generation

Prediction images were converted into videos using FFmpeg.

Example:

```bash
ffmpeg -framerate 5 -i frame_%04d.jpg output.mp4
```

Videos were further enhanced by stacking outputs and adding music.

